=========================
PreferencesKit 0.1 README
=========================

PreferencesKit is a framework which provides various features to build flexible Preferences-like window in any GNUstep or Cocoa applications. It includes an NSPreferencePane implementation (following Cocoa API).

It is based on GSSystemPreferences code written by Uli Kusterer.

This framework is released under LGPL license (see COPYING document).
Original licence of GSSystemPreferences is LGPL License too.

Maintainer: Quentin Mathe <qmathe@club-internet.fr>
Author: Uli Kusterer, Quentin Mathe, Yen-Ju Chen

To know more about PreferencesKit: 
<http://www.dromasoftware.com/etoile/mediawiki/index.php?title=PreferencesKit>


Build and Install
-----------------

Read INSTALL document.


Mac OS X support
----------------

PreferencesKit is compatible with Cocoa (Xcode project included).


Known issues
------------ 
 	 
     * Matrix presentation is not in a usable state currently
     * Table view (in Table presentation mode) doesn't always highlight the 
     selected row on GNUstep
     * Preference panes linked against Cocoa PreferencePanes framework cannot be 
     loaded (should be fixed in next version)


Developer notes
===============

Tests suite
-----------

UnitKit (bundled with Etoile) is required.

    Steps to produce a test bundle and run tests suite:

    * make test=yes 

    * ukrun PreferencesKit.bundle


Dependency
---------

None.


